# .npmignore — whitelist approach. The npm tarball ships only the runtime
# files the standalone CLI needs (R-N7, v0.9.0+). Plugin-only artifacts
# (bash hooks, slash commands, spec distribution, install/update scripts)
# stay out of the tarball — they're delivered to Claude Code via the
# marketplace clone path, not via npm install.
#
# Verify with: `npm pack --dry-run` (see "Tarball Contents" output).

# Default: ignore everything.
*

# Re-include the CLI's transitive surface.
!bin/
!bin/**
!scripts/
!scripts/lib/
!scripts/lib/lint.js
!hooks/
!hooks/banned-vocab.patterns
!package.json
!README.md
!CHANGELOG.md
!LICENSE
